  "datePublished": "2026-03-31",
  "description": "Spacetime is the four-dimensional continuum combining three spatial dimensions and one time dimension, in which all physical events occur. Special relativity (Einstein, 1905) demonstrated that space and time are not independent: the measured distance and duration between two events depend on the observer\u0026rsquo;s state of motion, but the spacetime interval between them does not. This interval \u0026ndash; roughly, the difference between squared time separation and squared spatial separation \u0026ndash; is the invariant quantity that all observers agree on.\n",
